   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <pb facs="#facs_1" n="1" xml:id="img_0001"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_1_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">Religious Art:</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_3" n="N002"/>I. Level: Every {Art} Style as the expression of Being.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_4" n="N003"/>(Examples from so called secular art):
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_5" n="N004"/>1. A Roman couple
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_6" n="N005"/>2. The Head of Seneca
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_7" n="N006"/>3. <rs type="person" key="da Messina, tillich_person_id__3990">Antonello da Messina</rs>: Portrait of a young man
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_8" n="N007"/>4. Ulm School: The Lovers.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_9" n="N008"/>5. <rs type="person" key="Velasquez, tillich_person_id__3991">Velasquez</rs>, Maria Anna, queen of Spain
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_11" n="N009"/>6. <rs type="person" key="Fragonard, tillich_person_id__3966">Fragonard</rs>: The Pursuit
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_12" n="N010"/>7. <rs type="person" key="Chardin, tillich_person_id__3992">Chardin</rs>: A boy, blowing bubbles.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_13" n="N011"/>8. <rs type="person" key="Toulouse-Lautrec, tillich_person_id__3993">Toulouse Lautrec</rs>: At the Moulin-Rouge, the Dance.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_14" n="N012"/>9. <rs type="person" key="seurat, tillich_person_id__1773">Seurat</rs>: La Grande Jatte
               <lb facs="#facs_1_tr_1_tl_15" n="N013"/>10. <rs type="person" key="Matisse, tillich_person_id__1276">Matise:</rs> Lemons against Pinc Background.
            </ab>
            <pb facs="#facs_2" n="2" xml:id="img_0002"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_2_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>11. etc. <Impressionism>Impressionists</Impressionism> (<rs type="person" key="Renoir, tillich_person_id__1583">Renoir</rs>, <rs type="person" key="Monet, tillich_person_id__1343">Monet</rs>, <rs type="person" key="Degars, tillich_person_id__442">Degas</rs>)
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>II Level: The style which aims at expression
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>(so called <Expressionism>expressionism</Expressionism> as a universal stlye)
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>1. Primitive masks
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>2. Archaic types
               <lb facs="#facs_2_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>3. Mosaics
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_2" n="N007"/>4. 
            </ab>
            <ab facs="#facs_2_r_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l_1" n="N001"/>
            </ab>
            <ab facs="#facs_2_r">
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l" n="N001"/>
            </ab>
            <pb facs="#facs_3" n="3" xml:id="img_0003"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_3_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l" n="N001"/><hi style="text-decoration: underline;">Wednesday</hi>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_3_tl_1" n="N002"/>Oct 8. Exploration of basic concepts: <Symbol>Symbol</Symbol> and <Language>Sign</Language>.
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>" 15. The 4 relations of <Religion>religion </Religion>and <Arts>art</Arts>.
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>" 22. Periods of Western <Arts>art</Arts> and <Religion>religion</Religion>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>" 29. Archaic, archaristic, <Expressionism>expressionistic</Expressionism>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>Nov. 12. Magic power and <Symbol>symbolism</Symbol>
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>" 19. Architectural symbolism
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_3_tl_8" n="N008"/>" 26. <Ontology>Ontology</Ontology> and abstract art.
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_3_tl_9" n="N009"/>Dez. 3. <Secular>Secular</Secular> <Religion>religious</Religion> <Arts>art</Arts>.
               <lb facs="#facs_3_l_1" n="N010"/>Dec. IV
               <lb facs="#facs_3_tr_3_tl_10" n="N011"/>" 17. Liturgical <Religion>religious</Religion> <Arts>art</Arts>
            </ab>
